Works very much like the linux ftp.

Just type a command followed by the appropriate value:

e.g > open ftp.mozilla.org



Commands:

open (value): Connects to ftp server

ls: Lists directory contents

pwd: Prints working directory

cd: Change working directory

bookmark (value): Bookmarks ftp server which connected to

bookmarks: Shows bookmarks

dirsize (value): Prints directory size

mkdir (value): Creates directory called value

download (value): Downloads file called value

upload (value): Uploads file to working directory

download -r (value): Recursively downloads directory called value

quit: Quits ftp client

